# TypeScript style

## Types

- Public shapes are declared with `interface`. Discriminated unions and type aliases use `type`. Example: `ConvertOptions`, `BuildHtmlOptions`, `DesignTokens`, `PaletteTokens` are interfaces; `RenderMode = 'light' | 'dark'` is a type.
- Never leak `any`. Normalize unknown errors with the project pattern:

```ts
} catch (err) {
  const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
  logger.error(message);
}
```

  Used in [src/cli.ts](src/cli.ts), [src/converter.ts](src/converter.ts), [src/repl.ts](src/repl.ts). Keep it.
- Prefer readonly input options where practical. Do not mutate caller-supplied options objects (the converter merges defaults via destructuring, not assignment).

## IO

- Async filesystem in hot paths: `import fsp from 'fs/promises'` and `await fsp.readFile/writeFile/mkdir`. The converter pipeline ([src/converter.ts](src/converter.ts)) is entirely async.
- Sync `fs.readFileSync` is only acceptable for one-shot CSS/asset loads that are cached for the process lifetime (see `readCss` cache in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts) and `resolveMermaidSrc` in [src/mermaid-runtime.ts](src/mermaid-runtime.ts)).
- When resolving local files for Chromium, always convert to a `file://` URL via `pathToFileURL` (see image rewriter in [src/markdown.ts](src/markdown.ts) and KaTeX font URLs in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts)).

## Concurrency

- The only concurrency primitive is `runPool` in [src/converter.ts](src/converter.ts). Do not introduce `Promise.all` over unbounded input.
- Long-running shared resources (the Puppeteer `Browser`) are launched once per run via `PdfRenderer.launch()` and closed in a `finally`. New modules that spawn external processes follow the same acquire/release pattern.

## String building for HTML & CSS

- HTML-escape every interpolated value before embedding in a template literal. Use the existing `escapeHtml` helpers in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts) / [src/markdown.ts](src/markdown.ts). Never inline user-controlled strings raw.
- CSS-escape strings that go into `content: "..."` (see `escapeCssString` in [src/template.ts](src/template.ts) for header/footer tokens).
